node.text:
The evenings are going to start getting cooler before we know it. The scramble to suck the marrow from another fleeting Maine summer is on, and we couldn’t think of a better vessel for these pursuits than Raspberry Granular. 

We’ve got a delicious array of food and drink to meet this beautiful Saturday with- reminder that @lakestreetdive ‘s sold-out show at @thompsonspoint is tonight, so expect a lively, busy environment after 3pm!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Bissell Brothers on August 20, 2021. May be an image of souvlakia.

node.text: Cooking on the line with hardwood charcoal today, and it feels so right- these @flyinggoatmaine loin skewers with pluots & tamarind pasilla pepper glaze come with gordita-style frybread, and it’s really whetting the whistle down here. Kitchen is going till 7, bar till 9-Brandy Carlisle was rescheduled to next week so should be easy in/out for delicious food & ice cold beer . 🍺🐐👍

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Bissell Brothers on August 20, 2021. May be an image of souvlakia.
Photo by Bissell Brothers on August 20, 2021. May be an image of food.
Photo by Bissell Brothers in Bissell Brothers. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text: The heat of August is perfect timing for an Outgrowth release 🌞🌱 This crispy pilsner features a hearty dose of fluffy Maine wheat, with New Zealand hops bringing some extra flavor to the party - delivering notes of white peach, chamomile, and plantain.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Bissell Brothers in Bangor, Maine. May be an image of 1 person and text that says '# bissellbrothers & Penquis Valley alumni present Masters 2021 Mainé Mini-Golf The Charity tournament to benefit M.S.A.D. #41'.

node.text:
The Maine Mini-Golf Masters are BACK this year! This creative tournament originated by Peter & Noah’s hometown schoolmates raises funds for projects in the Three Rivers area - and Bissell Brothers is committed to matching 100% of donations! If you can spare $5 to help our community, we’ll make it $10 - Our hometown has struggled through the pandemic like everyone else, but resources are already spread very thin. Any support is tremendously appreciated! 

Donation link in bio ⛳️ 🍺🏌🏼‍♀️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Bissell Brothers in Bissell Brothers. May be an image of drink.

node.text: After racking A Long Dusk off an absurd amount of Maine raspberries, we decided to refill the tank - fruit and all - with some of our gose, Granular. The resulting beer is an honest expression of the base integrated with the unmistakable flavor of fresh berry - with notes of salted melon, raspberry tea, and a picnic on a perfect beach day. Just arrived from @bbbthreerivers , available now to take home or enjoy in our taproom.

node.text: All this variety 🤤 Another @bbbthreerivers bottle is headed down to Portland — this time it’s Granular, a gose we first released back in April, aged on Maine raspberries. Outgrowth is finally back on Friday and we have TWO brand new beers on the horizon for next week. Stay tuned for more info!
